     <div type="poem">
   <head>
      <hi>To M</hi>
      <seg rend="sup">r</seg>. RAPH BLEVER-HASSIT</head>
   <l>NOt onely thy affection did I prise</l>
   <l>Showne to our Militarie exercise,</l>
   <l>When here I wrote thy name (deseruing <hi>Hassit</hi>)</l>
   <l>No, no: thy honestie, and vertue was it,</l>
   <l>That wonne me to this taske; then here I giue</l>
   <l>What next high heauen, may make the longest l iue.</l>
   <l>I hope youl' kindly take't; for I dare say,</l>
   <l>Such presents are not brought you euery day.</l>
</div>
